  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate the rate of false-positive results in Newborn
      Universal Hearing Screening Programs and it´s possible causes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      False-positive results in Newborn Hearing Screening(NHS) leads to unnecessary parents anxiety
      and increase the cost of the procedure before hospital discharge. Getting to know the
      possible causes will lead to solutions to decrease the number of normal hearing babies that
      fail NHS with Otoacoustic Emissions.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
